OL,3,CWales legend Terry Yorath dies aged 75
OL,5,FFormer Wales player and manager, Terry
OL,6,FYorath, has died aged 75 following a
OL,7,Fshort illness, his family have said in
OL,8,Fa statement.
OL,10,FBorn in Cardiff, Yorath played a big
OL,11,Fpart in the Leeds United team under
OL,12,FDon Revie, winning the First Division
OL,13,Ftitle, before spells with Coventry,
OL,14,FTottenham and Bradford. He also won 59
OL,15,Fcaps for Wales.
OL,17,FAfter his playing career, he went on
OL,18,Fto manage the national side in a five-
OL,19,Fyear spell in 1988 - including
OL,20,Fmasterminding a win over Brazil in
OL,21,F1991.
