OL,3,CWales legend Terry Yorath dies aged 75
OL,5,F"Our hearts are broken but we take
OL,6,Fcomfort knowing that he will be
OL,7,Freunited with our brother, Daniel."
OL,9,FThe former Wales captain played 141
OL,10,Ftimes for Leeds, scoring ten goals for
OL,11,Fthe Yorkshire club.
OL,13,FAs well as winning the First Division
OL,14,Fin 1974, he was part of a side that
OL,15,Fwere the runners up in the FA Cup and
OL,16,FEuropean Cup Winners' Cup in 1973, and
OL,17,FEuropean Cup in 1975.
OL,19,FYorath then played for Coventry for
OL,20,Fthree years before securing a #300,000
OL,21,Fmove to Tottenham Hotspur in 1979.
